sen babcock professor of food nutrition and public policy clark professor of entrepreneurship and professor of applied economics at cornell university will talk about new evidence on the linkages among agriculture nutrition and health with a special emphasis on south asia and or sub saharan africa currently lost in debate growing more food does not necessarily lead to better nutrition or health unless other things are put in place assistant professor eran bendavid from stanford's medical school infectious diseases will provide additional commentary bendavid was trained at harvard medical school and is currently a fse collaborator on a water related project that examines the links between food production health and nutrition per pinstrup andersen is babcock professor of food nutrition and public policy clark professor of entrepreneurship and professor of applied economics cornell university he was born in denmark and received his phd at oklahoma state university for many years he was the director general of the international food policy research institute in washington dc in 2001 he was named word food prize laureate pinstrup aandersen is a world renowned specialist on undernutrition health poverty and food location bechtel conference center encina hall 616 serra street stanford university stanford ca 94305 directions map fsi contact ashley dean parent research projects global food policy and food security symposium series fsi stanford fse series topics water south asia sub saharan africa search fse search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages events of interest modeling the effects of climate change on maize pests and pathogens and food security in east africa fsi stanford fse workshop woods institute food security salon rosamond l naylor david lobell walter p falcon pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford 